The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.2 percent to 14,442.18, while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  dropped 0.7 percent to 1,701.09.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates
 Colombia â€™s largest oil field, increased 1.6 percent to 48,480
pesos. Pacific Rubiales agreed to purchase 85.7 million units of
 CGX Energy Inc. (OYL)  to increase its stake in the oil explorer in
Guyana to 35 percent, according to a statement. CGX Energy
rallied 30 percent to 42 Canadian cents at the close in Toronto.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMGC)  , a Calgary-based  oil company 
that operates in the Andean region, gained 2.7 percent to 22,880
pesos. The shares climbed as crude advanced for a third straight
day in  New York  electronic trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
